(65, 1, '2011-07-26 14:57:49', '2011-07-26 21:57:49', '<p>In California, patients may legally choose any physical therapist they desire&mdash;even if your physician refers you to a specific physical therapy office, it is your choice where you seek treatment. If you would like to be treated by us, just ask your doctor! We have good relationships with local physicians.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can receive treatment without a physician’s prescription/referral. However, for insurance to cover treatment, a referral will be needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We accept most types of public and private insurance. As a courtesy, we confirm coverage prior to your first visit, so there are no surprises to you about the cost of your treatment. We offer a variety of payment plans to our patients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our purpose is to identify the cause of your symptoms and determine the best plan in treating\r\nthem. The first visit will include an assessment and then, patient and therapist will develop the most effective treatment plan.</p>\r\n', 'How to Become a Patient', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-3', '', '', '2011-07-26 14:57:49', '2011-07-26 21:57:49', '', 11, 'http://orovillephysicaltherapy.com/2011/07/11-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
