(105, 1, '2011-09-20 12:38:15', '2011-09-20 19:38:15', 'Valerie has 36 years of physical therapy experience, graduating from Loma Linda University, School of Allied Health Professions, in 1975. She worked in a variety of rehabilitation settings until opening her own practice in Oroville in 1984. While treating thousands of patients from Oroville and the surrounding communities, she has also developed her skills with continuing education programs that emphasize deferential diagnoses, manual therapy and evaluation/treatment techniques for musculo-skeletal disorders. She is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association, Orthopedic and Priavate Practice Sections.\r\n\r\nWhen not in the office, Valierie teachers toddlers and plays piano/organ for her church, loves traveling and visiting her children and new grandchild. She is committed to improving quality of life for people of her community by providing the best physical therapy care.', 'Valerie', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'valerie', '', '', '2011-09-20 12:43:39', '2011-09-20 19:43:39', '', 13, 'http://orovillephysicaltherapy.com/?page_id=105', 1, 'page', '', 0),
(106, 1, '2011-09-20 12:38:06', '2011-09-20 19:38:06', '<p>Valerie has 36 years of physical therapy experience, graduating from Loma Linda University, School of Allied Health Professions, in 1975. She worked in a variety of rehabilitation settings until opening her own practice in Oroville in 1984. While treating thousands of patients from Oroville and the surrounding communities, she has also developed her skills with continuing education programs that emphasize deferential diagnoses, manual therapy and evaluation/treatment techniques for musculo-skeletal disorders. She is a member of the American Physical Therapy Association, Orthopedic and Priavate Practice Sections.</p>\n<p>When not in the office, Valierie teachers toddlers and plays piano/organ for her church, loves traveling and visiting her children and new grandchild. She is committed to improving quality of life for people of her community by providing the best physical therapy care.</p>\n', 'Valerie', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '105-revision', '', '', '2011-09-20 12:38:06', '2011-09-20 19:38:06', '', 105, 'http://orovillephysicaltherapy.com/2011/09/105-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(107, 1, '2011-09-20 12:38:48', '2011-09-20 19:38:48', '<span style="font-family: Cambria; font-size: small;">Travis graduated from California State University Long Beach, and has been practicing physical therapy for eight years. Continuing education includes:</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Cambria; font-size: small;">Certification by Kenesio Taping Association International, certification in Integrated Neruomuscular Re-Education Muscle Energy, courses in Functional Biomechanics of the Lower Quarter, Grade V mobilization through California Orthopedic Manual Physical Therapy Special Interest Group. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Cambria; font-size: small;">Travis chose physical therapy because he wanted to make a difference with the hours he spends working. He enjoys seeing people walk out of the clinic with less pain, more mortion and more confidence in their abilities to return to living. As he studies the human body, Travis says its function creates in him a wonder in awe of God, which motivates him to learn more through the patients he sees each day.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Cambria; font-size: small;">Travis lives with his wife and their four boys in Oroville. They enjoy kayaking, camping, taking walks on the dam and riding bikes at Riverbend Park. Travis also enjoys coaching his sons in Oroville Youth Soccer, Upward Basketball and Junior Giant. </span>', 'Travis', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'travis', '', '', '2011-12-21 18:05:24', '2011-12-22 02:05:24', '', 13, 'http://orovillephysicaltherapy.com/?page_id=107', 2, 'page', '', 0),
