(109, 1, '2011-09-20 12:39:12', '2011-09-20 19:39:12', '<span style="font-family: Cambria; font-size: small;">Luke earned his undergraduate degree in Biological Sciences from UC Davis, and a Master''s degree in Physical Therapy through a joint program offered by San Francisco State and UC San Francisco. He has extensive training and continuing education in treatment of the neck, back, shoulders, knees, pelvis and hips, as well as training in Grade 5 Mobilization.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Cambria; font-size: small;">Luke was led to physical therapy by his interest in the sciences.  He enjoys working with different people daily and problem solving to meet their needs. By working as a physical therapist, Luke hopes to help others by helping people become more active and experience less pain and a better quality of life.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Cambria; font-size: small;">Luke lives in Oroville with his wife and two young children. He enjoys coaching his daughter in soccer and baseball, playing softball and riding ATVs.</span>', 'Luke', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'luke', '', '', '2011-09-20 12:43:51', '2011-09-20 19:43:51', '', 13, 'http://orovillephysicaltherapy.com/?page_id=109', 3, 'page', '', 0),
