(111, 1, '2011-09-20 12:39:37', '2011-09-20 19:39:37', '<span style="font-family: Cambria; font-size: small;">Kay graduated from the University of Colorado in 1999 with a Masters of Science in Physical Therapy. She was raised in Gridley and returned to her home state to pursue her career. In May 2010, Kay traveled to Washington and studied under Janet Hulme, a physical therapist who specialized in pelvic color rehabilitation. With a new interest and understanding of the pelvic floor rotator cuff, Kay launched her new Roll for Control pelvic floor rehabilitation program.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Cambria; font-size: small;">Kay aspired to work in the medical field from a young age, but wanted to work in a job that would allow flexibility to spend time with family as well as patient interaction. She feels rewarded by watching patients progress through their treatment plans and ultimately meet the functional goals set at the beginning of their treatment.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Cambria; font-size: small;">Kay has been married for 12 years. Her husband is also a physical therapist. They have two children and Kay keeps busy with their various athletic and social intersts. She also enjoys long walks, hikes and bike rides with her family.</span>', 'Kay', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'kay', '', '', '2011-09-20 12:43:58', '2011-09-20 19:43:58', '', 13, 'http://orovillephysicaltherapy.com/?page_id=111', 4, 'page', '', 0),
