(152, 2, '2011-12-21 18:13:18', '2011-12-22 02:13:18', '<em class="highlight">What is Physical Therapy?</em> Physical therapy is a profession in which the physical therapist empowers, educates and enables those with impairments, activity limitations, participation restrictions and disabilities to facilitate great independence, health, wellness and enhanced quality of life. <cite>California Physical Therapy Board Code of Ethics</cite>\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-127" title="" src="/assets/luke-working-199x300.jpg" alt="Luke Working" width="199" height="300" />\r\n\r\n<em class="highlight">Why Choose Valerie Nelson Physical Therapy?</em> Our mission is to provide top-quality, customized, physical therapy services in a caring and compassionate environment. <a href="/services">More in-depth information on the services we offer »</a>', 'Welcome to Valerie Nelson Physical Therapy', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '33-revision-28', '', '', '2011-12-21 18:13:18', '2011-12-22 02:13:18', '', 33, 'http://orovillephysicaltherapy.com/2011/12/33-revision-28/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
